{
  "texts": [
    "The TCNN architecture is tuned to achieve high accuracy in classification tasks with limited training data, and it demonstrates robustness against overfitting, as indicated by the testing results with different sizes of training datasets.",
    "However, the manual tuning of TCNN parameters like learning rate and neuron counts lacks a solid theoretical basis, requiring trial-and-error for high accuracy.",
    "The ability of the model to identify incomplete or partial specimens remains unexplored.",
    "Xu et al. (2022) present a multi-scale DL model classifying graptolite (colonial hemichordate macrofossils).",
    "This Multi-scale Learning Network may encounter challenges with highly varied or intricate backgrounds, as it depends on downsampling and set discriminative areas, diminishing its performance on diverse or cluttered datasets, but it was able to successfully classify graptolite fossils."
  ]
}